
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `file-roller` baraye baz kardan, sakhtan, va tagheer dadan file-haye zip shode (archive) estefade mishavad. In barname mesle yek sandogh baraye file-haye ziadi ast ke ba ham jam shodeand ta fazaye kamtari begirand ya rahattar share shavand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--extract-to=PATH`  --> 📤 File-haye dakhele archive ra dar yek poosheye moshakhas baz mikonad (extract mikonad).  Agar `PATH` ra nadeed, dar haman directory-ye fa'ali ke hastid baz mishavad.
    🔹 `--add-to=ARCHIVE`  --> ➕ File-haye entekhab shode ra be yek archive ezafe mikonad.  Agar `ARCHIVE` vojood nadashte bashad, yek archive jadid misazad.
    🔹 `--help` --> ❓ Namayeshe rahnamaye dastoor `file-roller`.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ file-roller archive.zip

    🔹 Baz kardane file-e `archive.zip` ba estefade az barnameye `file-roller`.

    $ file-roller --extract-to=/tmp archive.tar.gz

    🔹 Baz kardane file-e `archive.tar.gz` dar poosheye `/tmp`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ file-roller --add-to=my_archive.zip file1.txt file2.txt

    🔹 File-haye `file1.txt` va `file2.txt` be archive-e `my_archive.zip` ezafe mishavand.  Agar `my_archive.zip` vojood nadashte bashad, yek archive jadid ba in nam sakhte mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `file-roller` command is used to open, create, and modify archive files (like zip files).  It acts as a container for multiple files, allowing them to be compressed for smaller size or easier sharing.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--extract-to=PATH`  --> 📤 Extracts the files from the archive to a specified directory `PATH`. If `PATH` is not provided, it extracts to the current working directory.
    🔹 `--add-to=ARCHIVE`  --> ➕ Adds selected files to an archive.  If `ARCHIVE` doesn't exist, it creates a new archive.
    🔹 `--help` --> ❓ Displays the help message for the `file-roller` command.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ file-roller archive.zip

    🔹 Opens the `archive.zip` file using the `file-roller` application.

    $ file-roller --extract-to=/tmp archive.tar.gz

    🔹 Extracts the contents of `archive.tar.gz` into the `/tmp` directory.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ file-roller --add-to=my_archive.zip file1.txt file2.txt

    🔹 Adds the files `file1.txt` and `file2.txt` to the archive `my_archive.zip`. If `my_archive.zip` does not exist, a new archive with that name is created.
